org.processmining.models.heuristics.impl
Class ActivitiesMappingStructures

java.lang.Object
  org.processmining.models.heuristics.impl.ActivitiesMappingStructures

public class ActivitiesMappingStructures
extends java.lang.Object

Aids the creation of HeuristicsNets objects. In short, this class guarantees that indexes assigned to activities in HeuristicsNet objects are always the same whenever (i) XEventClasses objects have the same contents and (ii) the same number of activities must be created for a given XEventClass object.

Author:
Ana Karla Alves de Medeiros

ActivitiesMappingStructures

public ActivitiesMappingStructures(org.deckfour.xes.classification.XEventClasses events,
                                   java.util.Map<org.deckfour.xes.classification.XEventClass,java.lang.Integer> numberOfActivitiesPerEvent)
                            throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
Builds an ActivitiesMappingStructures that may contain duplicate activities for a given XEventClass. The exact number of activities by XEventClass event is provided in a mapping structure from XEventClass to Integer.

Note: Every event should have at least one activity assigned to it.

Parameters:
events - event classes to include in this ActivitiesMappingStructures object.
numberOfActivitiesPerEvent - mapping specifying the number of activities that should be created in this ActivitiesMappingStructures based on the provided XEventClass object.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if (i) the numberOfActivitiesPerEvent does not contain an entry for a given XEventClass object in events or (ii) the numberOfActivitiesPerEvent returns an Integer with value inferior to one 1 for this XEventClass object.
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
